# LED Strip Remapping Driver Configuration
menuconfig LED_STRIP_REMAP
    bool "LED Strip Remapping Driver"
    depends on LED_STRIP
    default y
    help
      Enable dynamic remapping and layered rendering for addressable LED strips (e.g., WS2812).
      Supports priority-based rendering (base layer → indicators → layer indicators) [1,2](@ref).

if LED_STRIP_REMAP

config LED_STRIP_REMAP_CHAIN_LENGTH
    int "Logical LED chain length"
    range 1 256
    default 10
    help
      Number of virtual LEDs in the remapping chain.
      Must match the value defined in the device tree [2,3](@ref).

config LED_STRIP_REMAP_MAX_LAYERS
    int "Maximum layer indicator groups"
    range 1 8
    default 3
    help
      Maximum number of independent layer indicator groups (e.g., for keyboard layers).
      Each group requires 4 pre-defined colors (RGB for layers 0-3) [5](@ref).

config LED_STRIP_REMAP_INDICATOR_PRIORITY
    bool "Enable indicator priority override"
    default y
    help
      Allow layer indicators to override base/indicator colors (highest priority).
      Disable this to reduce rendering overhead [1,7](@ref).

config LED_STRIP_REMAP_DYNAMIC_MAP
    bool "Support runtime remapping table"
    depends on !SMP
    default n
    help
      Enable dynamic remapping table updates at runtime.
      Note: Requires exclusive access to avoid concurrency issues [2,6](@ref).

config LED_STRIP_REMAP_DEBUG
    bool "Enable debug logs"
    default n
    depends on LOG
    help
      Enable verbose debugging output for rendering pipeline.
      Increases flash usage and reduces performance [4,5](@ref).

endif  # LED_STRIP_REMAP
